The paper discusses the recent advancements in deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and their applications in computer vision, image processing, natural language processing, and speech recognition. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the learning ability of deep CNNs, which falls under the category of machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The use of CNNs in natural language processing and speech recognition suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) could also be relevant sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the architectural innovations in CNNs, which could fall under the category of neural networks and their optimization, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category as well.
